HEADWORD: Douce
<hw>Douce</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>doux</ets>,
masc., <ets>douce</ets>, fem., sweet, fr. L. <ets>duleis</ets>
sweet.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Sweet; pleasant.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sober; prudent; sedate; modest.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And this is a <qex>douce</qex>, honest man.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Doucepere</ent>⟦br⟧
